
[1]swearing

   SWEARING, ppr. Affirming upon oath; uttering a declaration, with an
   appeal to God for the truth of it.

   1. Putting upon oath; causing to swear.

     SWEARING, n. The act or practice of affirming on oath. Swearing in
                              court is lawful.

   1. Profaneness. All swearing not required by some law, or in conformity
   with law, is criminal. False swearing or perjury is a crime of a deep
   dye.
